A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Legislative Services – Data Collection – Violent Crimes
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of State Police to submit certain information
4 collected through the Uniform Crime Reporting Program to the Department of
5 Legislative Services on or before a certain date each year and create a certain work
6 plan; requiring the Department of Legislative Services to submit certain reports to
7 the Governor and General Assembly; and generally relating to data collection,
8 violent crimes, and the Department of Legislative Services.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
10 Article – State Government
11 Section 2–1261
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – State Government
17 2–1261.
18 (a) On or before October 31 each year, the Department of Public Safety and
19 Correctional Services shall submit to the Department, in the form of electronic raw data,
20 de–identified and disaggregated by age, race, and sex, information required to be reported
21 to the Governor in accordance with § 3–207(a)(2) of the Correctional Services Article.
22 (b) (1) On or before November 30 each year, the Department of State Police
23 shall submit to the Department, in a format that the Executive Director requires, the
24 information collected in accordance with § 2–307(a)(2) of the Public Safety Article.
