12 (C) (1) ON OR BEFORE NOVEMBER 30 EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT OF
13 STATE POLICE SHALL SUBMIT TO THE DEPARTMENT, IN ELECTRONIC FORMAT,
14 INFORMATION COLLECTED THROUGH THE UNIFORM CRIME REPORTING PROGRAM
15 ON THE FOLLOWING CRIME CATEGORIES:
16 (I) CRIMINAL HOMICIDE;
17 (II) FORCIBLE RAPE;
18 (III) ROBBERY;
19 (IV) ASSAULT;
20 (V) BREAKING OR ENTERING;
21 (VI) LARCENY OR THEFT;
22 (VII) MOTOR VEHICLE THEFT; AND
23 (VIII) ARSON.
24 (2) THE INFORMATION REQUIRED TO BE SUBMITTED UNDER
25 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING
26 INFORMATION FOR EACH INCIDENT:
27 (I) OFFENSE, INCLUDING OFFENSE SUBTYPE;
28 (II) DATE, COUNTY, ZIP CODE, AND INCIDENT LOCATION;

