1 (III) WHETHER AN ARREST WAS MADE;
2 (IV) WHETHER AN INCIDENT WAS DESIGNATED A HATE INCIDENT
3 OR HATE CRIME;
4 (V) AGE, RACE, ETHNICITY, AND SEX OF VICTIM;
5 (VI) AGE, RACE, ETHNICITY, AND SEX OF OFFENDER;
6 (VII) LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCIES INVOLVED;
7 (VIII) CASE CLEARANCE STATUS; AND
8 (IX) IF THE OFFENSE IS ARSON, TYPE OF PROPERTY.
9 (3) THE DEPARTMENT OF STATE POLICE SHALL CREATE A WORK
10 PLAN THAT:
11 (I) IMPROVES AND STREAMLINES CRIME DATA COLLECTION
12 AND REPORTING WITH RESPECT TO THE UNIFORM CRIME REPORTING PROGRAM;
13 (II) OUTLINES POLICIES AND PROCEDURES TO COLLECT AND
14 MEASURE HATE INCIDENTS AND HATE CRIMES IN A MORE EFFICIENT MANNER; AND
15 (III) CREATES PROCEDURES THAT ALLOW VICTIMS TO EASILY
16 REPORT AND DESIGNATE AN INCIDENT AS A SUSPECTED HATE CRIME ON THE
17 APPROPRIATE FORMS.
18 (4) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REPORT TO THE GOVERNOR AND
